	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Being a Warrior</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 4:30 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=494><span id=Scholar>Braun</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>56 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This is correct.<br><br>Damage dealt out is nice, but not your primary concern.&nbsp;&nbsp;Your job is to piss off a mob and keep it pissed off at you no matter what.  As the mob is busy being mad at you and you do 80 dmg a round, the ranger and monk can whack away for 120 and the rogue can backstab for 400.<br><br>Warriors aren't the number one damage dealers, we aren't even second or third.  Its nice to do more damage, but if you have a choice between 20 more damage or 2 more AC, go with the AC.<br><br>I only use 2H when theres another warrior in group with higher AC/level because 2H greatly diminishes your ability to keep a mob pissed at you.</p>&nbsp;<br>Braun - 59ish Ogre Warrior<br>Torvonnilous</td></td></tr>
