	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=660><span id=Scholar>Marcus</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>A quick note from a caster's perspective ;)<br><br>Don't just be a meat wall.&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't just hit the taunt button and HOPE your casters are ok.  When things go wrong (believe me, they WILL go wrong), it's going to be up to you to make things right again.<br><br>This means you need to pay attention during a fight.  Watch the mob in front of you to make sure it stays there.  Watch over it's shoulder so you can see it's friends coming.  Watch the message bar for when your casters scream for help.  And keep an eye on everyone's hp bar too ... seeing the wrong person's bar start shrinking is a warning that things have gone wrong.  Oh yeah, and always check that everyone is ready before you pull.<br><br>Combat is a whole lot more interesting than just hitting the Taunt button and the Kick button =)<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
